> 
> Andre Hedrick wrote:
> > 
> > Well they should be there since I use them also for new hardware.
> 
> Unfortunately not here, see what happen with 2.2.12 and 2.3.26
> using the _same_ "hdc=none" boot parameter :
> 
> Good 2.2.12 boot:
> -----------------
> hda: WDC AC24300L, ATA DISK drive
> hdb: CRD-8322B, ATAPI CDROM drive
> ide0 at 0x1f0-0x1f7,0x3f6 on irq 14
> hda: WDC AC24300L, 4112MB w/256kB Cache, CHS=524/255/63, UDMA
> hdb: ATAPI 32X CD-ROM drive, 128kB Cache
> 
> Bad 2.3.26 boot:
> ----------------
> hda: WDC AC24300L, ATA DISK drive
> hdb: CRD-8322B, ATAPI CDROM drive
> hdc: WDC AC24300L, ATA DISK drive
> ide0 at 0x1f0-0x1f7,0x3f6 on irq 14
> ide1 at 0x170-0x177,0x376 on irq 15
> hda: WDC AC24300L, 4112MB w/256kB Cache, CHS=524/255/63, UDMA(33)
> hdc: WDC AC24300L, 4112MB w/256kB Cache, CHS=8912/15/63, UDMA(33)
> hdb: ATAPI 32X CD-ROM drive, 128kB Cache, DMA
> 
> As you can see 2.3.26 didn't show "ide_setup: hdc=none" debug line
> and I repeat, all hdx/idex cmdline was ignored :(
> 
idebus=... parameter (for PCI bus speed) is also ignored.
